a tiger escaped from its cage attacked a boy and 
triggered a panic that left 40 people unconscious during a circus 
in rural china a newspaper reported today 
the workers daily reported that the tiger broke out of its cage 
after being hit by its trainer for failing to carry out a trick 
during a show in northern chinas shanxi province last month 
it said 40 people were knocked unconscious when hundreds of 
spectators surged toward the exit one primary school student was 
attacked by the tiger and required 48 stitches in his face 
the daily did not say how the tiger was subdued and returned to 
its cage it said a similar accident involving the same circus 
troupe had occurred the previous month and called for improved 
safety measures 
