three pesticideladen helicopters took off on 
an aerial spraying mission thursday night to fight the medfly 
infestation that has set up a base in beverly hills and the citys 
toney west side 
theyre currently over beverly hills said tom kenney a 
federal aviation administration controller at santa monica airport 
where the choppers departed from shortly after 8 pm 
the spraying program is the first step in an allout attack 
against the mediterranean fruit fly a pest that destroys about 250 
varieties of produce 
the national weather service again forecast coastal fog for the 
area thursday night but officials moved the starting time up 2 
hours to 8 pm hoping to beat the rolling fog bank 
the spraying was ordered because 47 medflies were found in yards 
since sept 26 a serious infestation that if allowed to spread 
would threaten fruits and vegetables that are a major part of 
californias 155 billionayear farm economy 
the thursday flight was set for a 35squaremile area of 100000 
residents that includes middleclass stucco homes mansions swank 
rodeo drive shops and luxury car dealerships all subject to the 
honeylike stickiness of the malathion spray 
along with parts of beverly hills officials are spraying 
sections of western los angeles and the adjacent cities of culver 
city and west hollywood 
at martin cadillac on the corner of olympic boulevard and bundy 
drive in west los angeles a caravan of about 100 shiny caddies 
left the sales lot wednesday night for an underground parking lot 
at a bank building six blocks away sales manager steve mitchell 
said thursday 
he said several of the cars were returned to the sales lot 
thursday morning for potential tirekickers with the luxury car 
exodus to be repeated at nightfall 
the pesticide poses no health risks health officials say but 
the sticky corn syrup bait mixed with the malathion could mess up a 
cars paint job museums in the area covered their outdoor statues 
agricultural commissioner leon spaugy said the fight to save the 
states farm industry knows no economic boundaries 
were encouraging people to cover up their rolls royces just 
like they would cover up their pintos he said on wednesday 
