infantile attitude 
he said he believed us officials have recognized the 
importance of demand for illegal drugs in the problem of drug 
trafficking 
that is a great advance since you have to accept the reality 
that the united states is the biggest consumer of drugs in the 
world and that constitutes an enormous motive to promote production 
or transportation from other parts of the world he said 
he said there were slight and tenuous signs of understanding 
that the developing countries huge foreign debts have worldwide 
implications 
mexicos 104 billion foreign debt is the second highest in the 
