and vladimir trofimov were generally satisfied with the tour 
adding that this kind of inspection will help to build confidence 
measures in europe 
the inspectors arrived wednesday after giving britain the 
36hour minimum notice for an inspection as required under the 1986 
stockholm agreement for relaxing eastwest tensions 
they sought to assess the character and scale of drakes 
drum which britain described as a defensive eightday exercise to 
test protection of airfields ports and other installations 
