township near johannesburg police said 
a limpet mine placed in a trash bin also damaged windows and 
walls of the municipal building in tembisa east of johannesburg 
police added 
the victims included three men and three women police said the 
governmentrun south african broadcasting corp said one of the 
women was in serious condition 
there have been almost daily bombings in recent weeks in south 
africa the 29 bombings in september were the most ever in the 
country in a single month 
police have blamed virtually all of the attacks on the outlawed 
african national congress the main black guerrilla group 
attempting to overthrow the whiteled government 
police say the anc has intensified its bombing campaign in a bid 
to disrupt the nationwide municipal elections set for oct 26 
there have been about 150 bombings in south africa since the 
government declared a nationwide state of emergency in june 1986 
</TEXT>
