hundreds of children were vaccinated 
against polio friday in the first stage of a nationwide campaign to 
immunize all israelis up to the age of 40 against the disease 
the health ministry ordered the campaign after nine israelis 
were infected by polio which causes muscular paralysis 
in the next four weeks about 32 million people will be 
vaccinated said ministry spokesman shmuel algrabli 
israelis are immunized as children and the current vaccination 
is a booster 
the first stage of the campaign centered on the tel aviv suburb 
of rehovot and the northern coastal town of acco polio viruses 
were found in the sewage systems of both areas 
in rehovot hundreds of parents lined up at clinics with their 
infants large yellow wall posters informed residents when 
different age groups should report for vaccinations 
