<TEXT>
a felony court acquitted a greek 
businessman of espionage friday although he admitted giving 
details of the usbuilt stinger antiaircraft missile to the 
soviet union 
the threemember court said michalis megaloconomou was innocent 
on the ground the material handed over was not secret 
megaloconomou took unclassified materials for a wellknown 
weapons system the soviet union wasnt going to build anything 
from material it already had obtained from other people 
prosecutor constantinos androulikakis said in his summing up 
the 40yearold businessman told the court he gave 400 
microfiche cards to a soviet intelligence agent in april 1984 but 
didnt know they contained information on the shoulderfired 
stingers trigger system 
i thought they contained information on a telephone system 
he said 
megaloconomou also told the court he traveled to the soviet 
union in 1984 on a false passport and was given a miniature camera 
decoding pads and a radio receiver by a soviet agent 
the case was linked with the may 1985 defection in athens of 
soviet agent sergei bokhane whose revelations cast doubts on 
greeces capacity to safeguard nato secrets and delayed the sale of 
40 usmade jet fighters to greece 
brig ioannis alexakis a former head of counterintelligence 
for the greek central intelligence service told the court 
wednesday megaloconomou had been a soviet spy for 10 years when he 
was arrested in september 1985 
but the prosecutor addressing only the stinger case said we 
cant say he gave secrets to a foreign power and endangered the 
security of greece or its allies espionage is taking state secrets 
with the intent of harming the nation 
megaloconomou is a former deputy director at standard electric 
hellas or seh a greek company affiliated with the american 
international telephone amp telegraph corp itt 
also acquitted were two seh employees commercial director 
constantinos libousakis and secretary artmenis tzirozidou who were 
tried on misdemeanor charges in the same court for violating state 
secrets through negligence 
seh was among firms in six western european countries that 
manufactured stinger components under license 
megaloconomou was arrested on the basis of information given to 
the american cia by bokhane who served as deputy head of the 
soviet military intelligence agency gru in athens 
bokhane said megaloconomou was recruited by the gru in 1975 and 
began selling them information in 1977 according to alexakis 
in a 1986 trial a greek navy officer and a greek businessman 
accused of selling information and telecommunications equipment to 
moscow were acquitted on the ground that greek intelligence 
services couldnt confirm bokhanes allegations 
the united states delayed approving the sale of the f16 
jetfighters to greece until premier andreas papandreous socialist 
government signed an agreement in 1986 pledging to prevent advanced 
western technology from reaching the soviet union 
