<TEXT>
during 11 years as vice president to jomo 
kenyatta daniel arap moi says his job was to sing the tune of 
kenyas first president 
a decade after kenyattas death and mois emergence from an 
understudy to the mzee old man to the starring role in kenyan 
politics the schoolteacherturnedpresident has taught all 
wouldbe challengers to dance to his drums 
through shrewd political maneuvering the churchgoing 
teetotaling moi a member of the minority kalengin tribe has 
amassed power that rivals even the lionized kenyattas 
kenya is by law a oneparty state and moi is boss of the ruling 
kenyan african national union a body he says is supreme to the 
government 
parliament is essentially a rubber stamp to the presidents 
wishes and recent constitutional changes have brought the 
judiciary more under the executives control 
kenyatta too ran kenya with a tight rein and tolerated no 
dissent so pervasive was his rule that many doomsayers predicted 
kenya would be torn apart by tribal warfare after the death of 
kenyatta who was a member of the predominant kikuyu tribe 
but when the mzee died on aug 22 1978 moi the third and 
longestserving of kenyattas vice presidents peacefully succeeded 
him within 90 days as specified by the constitution moi called a 
presidential election he won it unopposed and was sworn in as 
kenyas second president oct 14 1978 the date he observes as the 
beginning of his presidency 
in the following months government officials released details 
of what they said had been a plot during kenyattas waning days to 
kill moi rather than allow the presidency to fall into the hands of 
a nonkikuyu 
though there were no arrests officials privately linked the 
plot to unidentified kenyatta aides and relatives who months before 
had tried unsuccessfully to thwart the constitutional transfer of 
power to moi 
moi retained many of kenyattas political allies although some 
were his political enemies it was only in september that he 
succeeded in ridding the party of the last vestiges of kenyattas 
power clique 
in a week of party elections beginning with grassroots 
balloting and ending with selection of national officers moi 
retained the party presidency kenyas supreme political job but 
the eight officers under him changed cementing mois power base 
during his 15 years of rule after independence from britain 
kenyatta would wave a flywisk his symbol of office and lead 
cheering crowds in kiswahili chants of harambee lets pull 
together 
moi saying he and the nation would be guided by the course 
kenyatta had charted adopted as his symbol of office and poer a 
