<TEXT>
the european economic community will 
not oppose japans request for a special international trade panel 
to resolve their dispute over the eec antidumping policy an eec 
spokeswoman said friday 
speaking on the condition of anonymity the spokeswoman said the 
eec was confident its policy conformed with international trade 
rules we are utterly serene about the formation of the panel 
said the official 
japan has contended that the eecs imposition of antidumping 
duties on locallyassembled japanese electronic typewriters and 
other products violates international trade rules 
specifically the japanese government believes that the eec is 
violating a rule of the general agreement on tariffs and trade that 
requires locally based foreign manufacturers to be treated in the 
same manner as their domestic counterparts 
a decision to form the panel likely will be made at a meeting on 
oct 19 of the gatt council the international trade body the 
spokeswoman said 
earlier this week the european court of justice rejected a 
complaint by a number of japanese companies that the commission 
used faulty accounting methods in antidumping cases 
